    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Kyle Tucker** (85.72) and **Gunnar Henderson** (83.18) stand as our offensive anchors. **Kyle Tucker** thrives in a prime matchup against Feltner, where the park factors and favorable platoon dynamics elevate his floor significantly, making him the safest high-upside play. **Gunnar Henderson** remains a must-start despite a minor rain risk (31%), as his spot at the top of the order and the favorable SP xERA of Williams provide the necessary leverage to drive scoring across R and RBI. Meanwhile, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) and **Andy Pages** (73.82) are the beneficiaries of strong matchup adjustments; **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** capitalizes on a favorable platoon edge against Houser, and **Andy Pages** is uniquely positioned to exploit Feltner\u2019s slow delivery, which boosts his stolen base potential despite hitting lower in the lineup.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Nasim Nunez**, whose 60.21 score was competitive but ultimately fell short of the starting rotation. While **Nasim Nunez** possesses the elite speed we covet for the SB category, the optimizer favored the higher raw offensive projections of **Josh Lowe** (72.21) and **Miguel Vargas** (64.21). **Josh Lowe** specifically earned the nod due to a superior matchup against M\u00e1rquez, where his combination of park favorability and platoon advantage outweighed the bench utility **Nasim Nunez** brings in a pinch-running scenario. We continue to monitor the lineup status for **Drake Baldwin**, **Gunnar Henderson**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**; should any of these middle-of-the-order threats be dropped, we may look to swap in **Marcell Ozuna** to stabilize our RBI output, provided the rain does not force a postponement in the games involving **Gunnar Henderson** or **Coby Mayo**.",
